{"data":{"docBySlug":{"html":"<h1 id=\"viewport-mercator-project\"><a href=\"#viewport-mercator-project\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>viewport-mercator-project</h1>\n<p>Projection and camera utilities supporting the Web Mercator Projection. At its core this is a utility for converting to and from map coordinates (i.e. latitude, longitude) to screen coordinates and back.</p>\n<h2 id=\"who-is-this-for\"><a href=\"#who-is-this-for\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Who is this for?</h2>\n<p>Specifically built for use with <a href=\"https://github.com/uber/deck.gl\">deck.gl</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/uber/react-map-gl\">react-map-gl</a>, but could be useful for any web mapping application that wants to support perspective enabled Web Mercator Projections with floating point zoom levels.</p>\n<h2 id=\"example-usage\"><a href=\"#example-usage\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Example Usage</h2>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">WebMercatorViewport</code> class offers the equivalent of a 3D matrix \"camera\" class of the type you would find in any 3D/WebGL/OpenGL library.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> WebMercatorViewport <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'viewport-mercator-project'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// A viewport looking at San Francisco city area</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> viewport <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">WebMercatorViewport</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  width<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">800</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  height<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">600</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  longitude<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">122.45</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  latitude<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">37.78</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  zoom<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">12</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  pitch<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">60</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  bearing<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">30</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nviewport<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">project</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">122.45</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">37.78</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// returns pixel coordinates [400, 300]</span>\nviewport<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">unproject</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">400</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">300</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// returns map coordinates [-122.45, 37.78]</span></code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"viewport-mercator-project Projection and camera utilities supporting the Web Mercator Projection. At its core this is a utility forâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"viewport-mercator-project","cover":"cover","category":"docs","tags":["default"]}}},"pageContext":{"relativeLinks":{"":"/docs","docs/README.md":"/docs","docs":"/docs","../api-reference/web-mercator-utils.md":"/docs/api-reference/web-mercator-utils","docs/api-reference/web-mercator-utils.md":"/docs/api-reference/web-mercator-utils","api-reference/web-mercator-utils":"/docs/api-reference/web-mercator-utils","docs/api-reference/web-mercator-utils":"/doc